    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A 12-Year-Old Boy, Killed in Gaza</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stuart Pilichowski letter asserts Israelis must be reminded to think optimistically during present turbulent rioting by Arabs both in Israel and in territories; holds process of negotiating must continue</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mideast Violence Continues to Rage; Death Toll Rises'' (front page, Oct. 1):</p>
        <p>Israelis must be reminded to think optimistically during the present turbulent rioting by Arabs both in Israel and in the territories. It's the first time in Israel's history that major roadways have been closed for the protection of the population at large.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mideast Violence Continues to Rage; Death Toll Rises'' (front page, Oct. 1):</p>
        <p>Israelis must be reminded to think optimistically during the present turbulent rioting by Arabs both in Israel and in the territories. It's the first time in Israel's history that major roadways have been closed for the protection of the population at large.</p>
        <p>My job takes me throughout Israel and into Jordan; my travels are easier and calmer in neighboring Arab Jordan than in Israel during the current unrest.</p>
        <p>The process of negotiating must continue. It's only when the two sides come to an agreement that peace can come to the area.</p>
        <p>STUART PILICHOWSKI  Ginot Shomron, Israel, Oct. 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
